  "prompt": "What is the gis?",
  "response": "GIS stands for Geographic Information System. It is a computer-based tool used for capturing, storing, analyzing, and displaying geographic or spatial data. GIS allows users to:\n\n1. Create interactive maps\n2. Analyze geographical relationships\n3. Visualize spatial information\n4. Integrate different types of data based on location\n\nGIS is used in various fields such as:\n- Urban planning\n- Environmental management\n- Transportation\n- Public health\n- Natural resource management\n- Emergency response\n- Agriculture\n- Archaeology\n- Business logistics\n\nKey features of GIS include:\n- Spatial data mapping\n- Geographic data visualization\n- Complex spatial analysis\n- Data layer integration\n- Geographical querying and research\n\nExamples of popular GIS software include ArcGIS, QGIS, and Google Earth.",
